Fringing Reefs:  these grow directly against a rocky coast.  Width varies up 
to a few hundred meters.  See Figure 5-16.  
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

 
 

Atolls:  ring-shaped reefs, unconnected with land.  These presumably 
developed as fringing reefs around oceanic islands that later subsided while reef 
growth kept pace with subsidence.  See Figure 5-17.  
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 
 

