by proposing that most limestones can be treated as particulate rocks involving 
framework, matrix, and cement just like siliciclastic rocks.  Although the terms he 
coined for the various classificatory categories are not widely used these days, his 
ideas have been of great significance.   
9.3.2  Folk called the coarse clastic constituents allochems.  These are the 
kinds described in an earlier section:  intraclasts, skeletal grains, ooids, and 
pellets.  He used the term micrite for the carbonate mud (short for microcrystalline 
